A moment of the father of the bride and his little girl before he walks her down the aisle. The father of the bride plays a major role in presenting the bride to her soon-to-be-husband; and it's a symbolic gesture and a timeless tradition around the world.

What is your favorite moment of a wedding?

Here are some of the reasons why we always recommend our couples to do a first look:
- It’s a special moment for you to look back on.
- It will calm your nerves.
- You will have a private and intimate moment before the ceremony.
- If you do cry, you will be able to freshen up before you go down the aisle.
Either you do a first look or not, that feeling of walking down the aisle doesn’t go away!

Have we convinced you yet?

When it comes to bridal shoes shopping, there are so many options that come into mind. Either it's heels or flats, elegant and systematic, you will want to guarantee all-day-comfort for the foot. One of our top pieces of advice is to bring an extra pair of shoes for your comfortness and have your bridesmaid keep them. Take this advice, you will thank us later.

What better way to surprise your guests than with a cyclo bridal entrance to the wedding? Tess and Andy have lived in Vietnam for years and they greatly embrace the country's culture. Hence why we add cyclos to the wedding program to emphasize a local spirit meanwhile making it a one-of-a-kind celebration.
